Kensa release verification keys
================================

This file holds the two public keys used to verify the integrity of
Kensa release artifacts published at
https://github.com/Hanalyx/kensa/releases.

You only need one or both depending on which artifact you're verifying:

  * `kensa-*.rpm`, `kensa-*.deb`             →  Hanalyx LLC GPG public key
                                               (the OpenPGP block below)
  * `kensa_<v>_checksums.sha256.sig`         →  Kensa cosign public key
                                               (the PEM block at the bottom)

Verification commands (copy-paste straight from the docs/guide/01-install.md
chapter — kept here as a fallback if the install guide is unreachable):

  # 1. Import the Hanalyx GPG key into rpm + dnf + apt trust stores
  sudo rpm --import https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Hanalyx/kensa/main/KEYS
  # or for apt:
  curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Hanalyx/kensa/main/KEYS \
    | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/hanalyx.gpg

  # 2. After downloading kensa_<v>_linux_<arch>.rpm:
  rpm --checksig kensa_<v>_linux_<arch>.rpm
  # expected:  Signature: ... key ID e239e50c: OK
  #            (Hanalyx LLC (release signing) <ops@hanalyx.com>)

  # 3. After downloading kensa_<v>_checksums.sha256 + .sig:
  cosign verify-blob --key cosign.pub \
    --signature kensa_<v>_checksums.sha256.sig \
    kensa_<v>_checksums.sha256

  # 4. Then verify every artifact you downloaded against the checksums:
  sha256sum -c kensa_<v>_checksums.sha256



